AVRDUDE WebAssembly notice
==========================

This Web AVR Programmer is designed to use the archived Leaphy Robotics
AVRDUDE WebAssembly fork as its programming engine:

  https://github.com/leaphy-robotics/avrdude-webassembly

The audited fork state for this prototype was tag v1.7.1 / commit b1ade73.
Its CMake project declares AVRDUDE version 7.3.

AVRDUDE and the WebAssembly port are GPL software. The ESP32 Bit Pirate Web
Tool UI must not present AVRDUDE, AVR part definitions, programmer drivers,
Intel HEX parsing, fuse handling, lock-bit handling, or ISP page programming as
original ESP32 Bit Pirate code.

Visible attribution used by the page:

  Powered by AVRDUDE WebAssembly and the ESP32 Bit Pirate AVR programmer adapter.

Local integration notes:

- The UI calls an isolated AvrdudeEngine API.
- AVRDUDE command construction is limited to high-level operations.
- The intended programmer is `-c buspirate`.
- The Web Serial port is bound through the existing WebAssembly serial bridge.
- Destructive operations require prior detection or explicit manual selection.
